rt-news/major-oak-the-1200-year-old-tree-with-ties-to-the-robin-hood-legend-is-presumed-dead-after-failing-to-produce-leaves-180988986/</guid></item><item><title>这家摄影工作室捕捉了南方黑人生活的美丽。很快，曾经隐藏起来的档案馆将拥有一个新的博物馆所在地</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-photography-studio-hooks-brothers-captured-the-beauty-of-black-life-in-the-south-soon-its-archive-once-hidden-away-will-have-a-new-museum-home-180988982/</link><description>胡克斯兄弟记录了 20 世纪孟菲斯的生活和欢乐。他们的照片将在孟菲斯艺术博物馆开放时向公众展示</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 19:15:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-photography-studio-hooks-brothers-captured-the-beauty-of-black-life-in-the-south-soon-its-archive-once-hidden-away-will-have-a-new-museum-home-180988982/</guid></item><item><title>天文学家通过回望时间边缘，发现了正在形成的“宇宙化石”——迄今为止所见过的化学性质最原始的星系</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-discovered-a-cosmic-fossil-in-the-making-the-most-chemically-primitive-galaxy-seen-yet-by-peering-back-to-the-edge-of-time-180988954/</link><description>詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜使用像放大镜一样的较近的星系团观察了 130 亿年前的光。这项工作帮助专家了解宇宙中最早的恒星和神秘的超微弱矮星系</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:41:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-discovered-a-cosmic-fossil-in-the-making-the-most-chemically-primitive-galaxy-seen-yet-by-peering-back-to-the-edge-of-time-180988954/</guid></item><item><title>这位被奴役的艺术家在巨大的罐子上签名，反抗了南方的扫盲禁令。现在，他的杰作与著名的保罗·里维尔碗一起展出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/by-signing-his-name-to-massive-jars-this-enslaved-artist-david-drake-defied-literacy-bans-in-the-south-now-his-masterpiece-is-on-view-with-a-famed-paul-revere-bowl-180988964/</link><description>大卫·德雷克 (David Drake) 于 1800 年左右出生于奴隶家庭，是一位技艺精湛的陶艺家。他的作品将在波士顿美术博物馆展出，以纪念美国成立 250 周年</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:29:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/by-signing-his-name-to-massive-jars-this-enslaved-artist-david-drake-defied-literacy-bans-in-the-south-now-his-masterpiece-is-on-view-with-a-famed-paul-revere-bowl-180988964/</guid></item><item><title>研究人员发现隐藏在常见室内植物叶子中的用于城市规划的数学模式</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-find-a-mathematical-pattern-used-in-city-planning-hidden-in-the-leaves-of-a-common-houseplant-180988978/</link><description>中国金钱树叶子的主脉形成了所谓的沃罗诺伊图。它可能是由植物生长激素引起的，这种激素从发育中的叶子毛孔中散发出来</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:02:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-find-a-mathematical-pattern-used-in-city-planning-hidden-in-the-leaves-of-a-common-houseplant-180988978/</guid></item><item><title>几乎所有植物都依赖于微小的地下真菌。微生物庞大的全球网络刚刚被首次绘制出来</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-all-plants-depend-on-tiny-underground-fungi-the-microbes-vast-global-networks-were-just-mapped-for-the-first-time-180988955/</link><description>如果首尾相连，构成地球表土中丛枝菌根真菌网络的细管状线可以在我们的星球和太阳之间伸展近十亿倍</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-all-plants-depend-on-tiny-underground-fungi-the-microbes-vast-global-networks-were-just-mapped-for-the-first-time-180988955/</guid></item><item><title>1775 年 6 月，美国爱国者队在邦克山战役中与英国人对峙。考古学家正在发现 251 年后的战斗证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-june-1775-the-american-patriots-faced-off-with-the-british-at-the-battle-of-bunker-hill-archaeologists-are-uncovering-evidence-of-the-fighting-251-years-later-180988979/</link><description>研究人员在波士顿查尔斯顿附近发现了枪支零件、步枪子弹和其他文物</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-june-1775-the-american-patriots-faced-off-with-the-british-at-the-battle-of-bunker-hill-archaeologists-are-uncovering-evidence-of-the-fighting-251-years-later-180988979/</guid></item><item><title>在国王曾经居住过的英国寄宿学校发现了可追溯到亨利八世统治时期的隐藏隧道</title><link>https://www.s